<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 8 月 10 日星期四 10:07:07 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Kim Yo Jong: What We Know About Kim Jong Un’s Sister and Her Role in North Korea]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这位独裁者的妹妹拥有明星影响力，政治形象不断上升，被称为该国事实上的二号人物<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11793591577686923893604587148733765658576"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-270505?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">金与正（照片摄于 2018 年）作为其兄长朝鲜领导人金正恩的红颜知己和顾问而声名鹊起。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Ryu Seung-Il/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11793591577686923893604587148733765658576"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/timothy-w-martin" itemprop="url" rel="author">蒂莫西·W·马丁</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日上午 3:27（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-sister-kim-yo-jong-11607524273"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>据首尔情报机构称，金与正据信至少 34 岁，是一名朝鲜高级官员，帮助监督该国对美国和韩国的政策，该机构称她为该国事实上的二号人物。</p><p>在她的各种头衔中，金正恩名义上是朝鲜宣传和鼓动部门的负责人。她在过去几年中声名鹊起，作为后者的红颜知己和顾问参加了时任总统唐纳德·特朗普和朝鲜领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/kim-jong-un">金正恩</a>之间的所有三次面对面会议。 2021年9月，她晋升为朝鲜最高决策机构国务委员会成员。最近，她<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-accuses-u-s-spy-plane-of-territorial-intrusion-422bafa3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">通过官方媒体攻击</a>美国、韩国和其他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-yo-jong-blasts-skeptics-of-north-koreas-military-advances-11671526251?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">怀疑金氏政权的</a>国家。</p><h3>金与正是谁？我们对她了解多少？</h3><p>金与正的确切出生日期尚不清楚，但韩国统一部的朝鲜官员数据库显示她于 1988 年出生于平壤。她是金正恩的妹妹，也是其父亲金正日最小的女儿，金正日于 1994 年至 2011 年间统治朝鲜，并与多名妇女育有子女。在她早年的时候，金女士是一个默默无闻的人物。这种情况在 2009 年发生了变化，当时有传言说，在他们的父亲<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204791104577107922829964182?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">遭受一系列中风</a>之后，金正恩被任命为朝鲜领导层的继承人。那年，官方媒体上展示了一张并排的照片，推测是她与金正恩和他们的长兄金正哲在一起的照片。 2011 年初，新闻摄像机还发现了她，当时<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-KRTB-1655?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">她与钟哲 (Jong Chol) 一起参加了新加坡埃里克·克莱普顿 (Eric Clapton) 的演唱会</a>。</p><p>她的婚姻状况不得而知，不过一些韩国新闻媒体提到她可能嫁给了朝鲜一位著名官员崔龙海(Choe Ryong Hae)的儿子，崔龙海是金正恩的国家事务委员会副手，该委员会是政府最有权势的决策机构。朝鲜官方媒体尚未公开看到她与丈夫在一起。随着金正恩在过去十年中<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-is-accelerating-plan-to-land-missiles-in-u-s-1494792608?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">加速朝鲜核武器发展</a>，自2018年以来参加涉及美国和韩国的核谈判，金正恩稳步获得国际知名度。2020年，当她的哥哥<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/as-kim-jong-un-disappears-north-korea-watchers-advise-caution-11587918517?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">被传病重</a>时，朝鲜专家提到如果她的兄弟突然去世或丧失行为能力，她可能会成为紧急后备人员。</p><p>她拥有成为朝鲜最高领导人的一个关键要求： <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/who-would-succeed-kim-jong-un-in-north-korea-look-to-mount-paektu-11588179168?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">她来自“白头山血统”，</a>或者说与该国创始人金日成有直系血统的人。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-270502?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2018年，两兄妹在分隔两国的非军事区内会见了韩国总统文在寅。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：韩国峰会新闻发布会</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>她在朝鲜的政治角色是什么？</h3><p>据首尔政府称，金女士至少从 2014 年起就在朝鲜政府担任正式职务，并在该国的橡皮图章议会中任职。她还在执政的工人党中央委员会（该党的执行机构）任职。 2018年，她作为哥哥的特使<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/south-korean-president-to-meet-kim-jong-uns-sister-1518081856?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">前往韩国</a>讨论朝鲜如何参加当年在韩国平昌举办的冬季奥运会，受到了国际关注。她后来<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amid-tense-geopolitical-backdrop-pyeongchang-opening-ceremony-stresses-harmony-1518176121?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">出现在奥运会开幕式上，</a>坐在当时的副总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/mike-pence">迈克·彭斯</a>旁边。她成为已知的第一位访问韩国的朝鲜执政金氏家族成员。</p><p>随后，金正恩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-heralds-very-comprehensive-agreement-with-kim-jong-un-1528783602?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">以她哥哥的知己和顾问的身份前往新加坡</a>、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-north-koreas-kim-end-nuclear-summit-early-11551334804?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">越南和朝韩边境</a>， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-says-north-koreas-kim-wants-to-meet-11561862697?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">参加她哥哥和特朗普之间前所未有的</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-says-north-koreas-kim-wants-to-meet-11561862697?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">面对面会面</a>。</p><p> 2020年3月，朝鲜政府首次以她的名义发表声明。该声明谴责韩国批评金氏政权几天前进行的军事演习。此后，她成为朝鲜公开谈论美国和韩国事务的首选人物。</p><p>此后，金与正警告拜登政府“制造臭味”，抗议华盛顿-首尔联合军事演习，并嘲笑韩国总统尹锡烈的和解尝试。</p><h3>她是下一个接替金正恩的人吗？</h3><p>没有任何公开的规则可以准确地概述朝鲜的领导层继任者。但自 1948 年建国以来，在该国发生的两次继任中，现任领导人都亲自挑选并培养了一名成年儿子，在他去世后接替他。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>家庭事务</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/who-would-succeed-kim-jong-un-in-north-korea-look-to-mount-paektu-11588179168?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">谁将在朝鲜接替金正恩？眺望白头山</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/south-korean-president-to-meet-kim-jong-uns-sister-1518081856?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">金正恩的妹妹、韩国领导人将共进午餐</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-will-send-his-sister-to-the-winter-olympics-1517990328?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">金正恩妹妹将出席奥运会</a></li></ul></div></div><p>据长期朝鲜观察人士称，如果现任金正恩突然去世或患重病，金正恩可能会成为临时摄政王，继承朝鲜的领导权。 2020 年 4 月，人们普遍猜测她的兄弟可能丧失行为能力或死亡，金与正被视为潜在的替补。这是因为她与执政的金氏家族有血缘关系，金正恩的所有孩子都在 18 岁以下，而且金氏家族的其他男性成员被视为在政治上被边缘化。同年 8 月，首尔情报机构称金正恩是平壤事实上的二号人物，尽管她可能不是官方指定的继承人。</p><h3>她和金正恩是什么关系？</h3><p>朝鲜专家表示，金与正很可能是金正恩唯一信任的顾问，因为他们有共同的血统，而且金与正并不引人注目。</p><p>金经常表现出帮助她的兄弟脱颖而出，而不是争夺权力或公众关注。朝鲜官方媒体将她描述为以副手身份陪同哥哥正式访问该国的工厂、农田和政府办公室，静静地提供建议和帮助，并手里拿着笔记本。朝鲜专家表示，她的年轻也被视为赢得朝鲜领导人信任的一大优势，因为在韩国文化中，年龄是资历的决定因素。</p><p>有传言称，2019 年 2 月的河内峰会未能达成无核化协议后，金正恩被降职。但她又恢复了该国政治局委员的职位，并参加了她哥哥的许多展示活动——包括 2020 年 5 月， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-is-said-to-have-attended-factory-opening-11588374281?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">金正恩在世人猜测他可能已经去世后再次出现在一家工厂的开业典礼上</a>。</p><p> 2022 年 11 月，金正恩在庆祝朝鲜的火星 17 号洲际弹道导弹发射时哭泣，这是朝鲜的一件大事。金正恩被拍到<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-koreas-kim-jong-un-puts-daughter-on-view-at-icbm-launch-11668844562?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与他的女儿以及金正恩的侄女手牵手</a>，这是这位朝鲜领导人的孩子首次公开露面。</p><p>她与哥哥的关系与他们的父亲金正日和他的妹妹金敬姬之间的关系进行了比较，金敬姬是朝鲜统治者唯一幸存的同父异母的兄弟姐妹。两人有着悲惨的过去：他们的母亲在他们还是孩子的时候就在难产时去世了，而另一位兄弟则一年前在一次溺水事故中丧生。金敬姬通过监督该国部分共产主义经济并担任顾问来帮助她哥哥的统治。但作为金正恩掌权后的姨妈，她的公共生活一直处于边缘化状态，而她的丈夫张成泽 (Jang Song Thaek) <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303932504579254632008825604?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">则被清洗并据信</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702304403804579259603815824842?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">于 2013 年被处决。金敬姬 (Kim Kyong Hui) 最近被拍到在 2020 年 1 月</a>参加一场音乐会与金正恩在平壤。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-270524?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">金正恩在劳动党中央委员会任职。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：新闻池</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>朝鲜人如何看待金与正？</h3><p>由于威权政府有能力处决哪怕是稍微批评金氏政权的公民，因此不可能准确衡量她在整个朝鲜公众中的地位。但公众可能不习惯让年轻女性担任高级政府职位，因为朝鲜担任此类职位的绝大多数都是年长男性。不过，她与哥哥金正恩的关系意味着她可以要求朝鲜精英的尊重——无论是真实的还是假装的——这些人大多居住在首都平壤。 2018年，当两人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-will-send-his-sister-to-the-winter-olympics-1517990328?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">率领朝鲜代表团访问韩国时，89岁的金永南——当时的朝鲜名义上</a>的国家元首，作为该国橡皮图章立法机构的负责人——向金永南鞠躬致敬。在韩国新闻摄像机前。</p><h3>国外对她的评价如何？</h3><p>由于她与金正恩的关系以及参加与美国、中国和韩国的重要外交会议，她被视为朝鲜领导人有影响力的助手。她在 2020 年针对韩国高级官员（包括总统文在寅）的严厉言论被首尔官员视为不同寻常，因为他们在最近的朝韩会议上与金正恩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-south-korea-meeting-to-determine-their-future-ties-1524749462?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">进行了私人谈话和饮酒</a>。大多数人记得她说话轻声细语，彬彬有礼。</p><p>在美国，她有时被认为是伊万卡·特朗普的非官方对手，伊万卡·特朗普曾担任她父亲的顾问，并陪同他进行与朝鲜的外交接触。两人还在2018年冬奥会上有过交集。金正恩作为朝鲜代表团非正式团长出席开幕式， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/winter-olympics-wind-down-with-plenty-of-razzle-dazzle-1519566208?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">特朗普作为美国代表团团长出席闭幕式</a>。</p><p>金还被人权组织和美国政府视为侵犯人权的同谋。他们说，她在朝鲜的高级职位使她对金氏政权持续处决、监禁和压迫政治犯负有部分责任。美国财政部 2017 年 1 月将她<a href="https://www.treasury.gov/press-center/press-releases/Pages/jl0699.aspx" target="_blank" class="icon none">列入制裁名单时表示，她在政府宣传部门的角色也将她</a>与金氏政权的审查活动联系起来。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D674FCDB-D28A-4110-9067-FE29751E77AA&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fkim-jong-un-sister-kim-yo-jong-11607524273&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">就在乔·拜登就职前几天，朝鲜推出了新型潜射弹道导弹，并将美国列为其最大的敌人。 《华尔街日报》的蒂莫西·马丁解释了为什么平壤希望成为华盛顿议程的首要议题。照片：KCNA/EPA/Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div><p><strong>写信给</strong>Timothy W. Martin，邮箱为<a href="mailto:timothy.martin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">timothy.martin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:27:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-sister-kim-yo-jong-11607524273</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-sister-kim-yo-jong-11607524273<author><![CDATA[Timothy W. Martin]]></author><category> NK实验</category><category>搜索引擎优化解释者</category><category>搜索引擎文章</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>NK实验</category><category>SEO解释者</category><category>搜索引擎文章</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>金正日</category><category>金永南</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Investment Ban on China Poised to Deepen Divide]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>拜登总统的命令是在中国经济放缓、新冠疫情封锁以及两国之间紧张关系加剧的背景下发布的<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833088?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：POOL/来自路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/charles-hutzler" itemprop="url" rel="author">查尔斯·赫茨勒</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日上午 12:28 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——经过多年将中国企业列入黑名单并审查它们在美国的投资，拜登政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">正在向美国企业发出明确的信号</a>，要求其将投资从中国转移出去。</p><p>拜登总统周三发布的一项行政命令虽然狭隘地针对具有军事、监视和网络能力的关键前沿技术，但更广泛的目标是重新安排美国资本和专业知识从其<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最大的全球竞争对手的</a>流动。</p><p>该命令禁止美国投资<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-u-s-uses-supply-chain-sway-to-throttle-chinas-chip-development-11666526403?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">先进半导体</a>和量子计算，并要求美国投资者就其他类型半导体和人工智能的投资通知华盛顿。它还禁止美国公民和永久居民参与违禁交易。</p><p>白宫官员表示，该命令旨在剥夺中国获得美国风险投资和私募股权公司投资带来的技术诀窍、市场准入和其他好处。除了中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济增长疲软</a>、新冠疫情封锁导致前往中国变得困难，以及最近在华盛顿和北京之间紧张局势加剧之际，针对美国和其他外国公司的施压行动，这可能会进一步扰乱在中国开展业务的美国公司。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833086?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登总统的命令针对的是具有军事、监视和网络能力的关键前沿技术。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>精品研究公司Trivium China的合伙人安德鲁·波尔克(Andrew Polk)表示，虽然他所建议的美国公司仍然对中国市场感兴趣，但许多公司已经变得犹豫不决。</p><p> “我们总是说——这引起了我们客户的共鸣——中国的风险调整回报已经发生了巨大变化，”波尔克说。 “所以我们看到很多公司从根本上重新思考他们的中国战略。这并不意味着他们一定会改变它们，但他们现在正在对它们进行压力测试，因为我们显然处于一个新环境中。”</p><p>周三的命令是在华盛顿和北京在台湾、乌克兰战争、间谍活动和技术控制等问题上经历了数月的严重紧张关系之后，正处于脆弱的关系之中。官员和安全专家表示，短期内，近几个月<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/janet-yellen-says-u-s-china-making-progress-on-managing-economic-tensions-1e2c07?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">脆弱的外交进展</a>可能会持续下去。</p><p>中国领导人习近平认为，在经济陷入通货紧缩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">、增长放缓和外国投资大幅下降之际，</a>与美国关系的平静（至少是暂时的）可以提升他在国内的威望。中国外交部高级官员杨涛上周在华盛顿与国务院和其他官员进行了讨论，重点是为习近平出席11月在旧金山举行的亚太领导人峰会以及与拜登举行单独会谈做准备据了解讨论情况的人士透露。</p><p>官员们表示，双方还推动修复沟通渠道，本月初步同意成立工作组来讨论亚太地区和海事问题。目前仍在讨论商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多（Gina Raimondo）是否可能在本月晚些时候访问北京，这将是拜登政府高级官员自 6 月以来第四次访问北京。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=607DAEAC-FDF3-4309-B753-4A08C846B405&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">从喷气式飞机到电动汽车再到超级计算机，《华尔街日报》与不同的行业和技术专家讨论了两国在设计、工程和战略方面的匹配情况。照片插图：迈克尔·塔布和盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>然而，从长远来看，美国和中国陷入竞争，迫使两国割裂数十年来稳定两国关系的经济和商业联系，而新的投资限制可能会加速两国进一步分裂的势头。</p><p> “关于多元化、去风险、脱钩、解开的言论——选择你的‘D字’，无论你喜欢哪个——它确实已经深入华盛顿的头脑，越来越多地在硅谷，而且这确实是在华尔街传播的前国家安全委员会官员丽莎·托宾 (Liza Tobin) 表示，她目前在华盛顿的一个专门研究技术政策的组织“特别竞争研究项目”工作。</p><p>曾经大力涌入中国的风险投资公司已经退出，部分原因是紧张局势加剧； Crunchbase 的数据显示，从 2021 年到 2022 年，美国对中国初创企业的投资下降了 30% 以上，今年还将进一步下降。</p><p>例如，据一位知情人士透露，总部位于加利福尼亚州的风险投资公司 Lightspeed Venture Partners 于 2006 年成立了中国分部，由于风险原因，该公司已削减了对中国初创企业的投资。</p><p>保卫民主基金会研究员、供应链情报公司 Horizo​​n Advisory 联合创始人内特·皮卡西克 (Nate Picarsic) 表示，“这一举措传达的真正信息是，这是一条持久的轨迹”，公司和投资者必须考虑这一点。 “地缘政治和国家安全风险已成为永久性的问题。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833087?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">随着中国从疫情中恢复过来，今年的经济增长出现了放缓。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：TINGSHU WANG/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>随着近几个月行政命令的形成，中国官员敦促美国不要通过该命令，并指责华盛顿试图阻碍中国的发展。该命令周三公布后，中国驻华盛顿大使馆表达了北京方面的失望，并表示美国正在将贸易武器化，并在维护经济关系的声明上出尔反尔。</p><p> “美方一再表示无意与中国‘脱钩’，但实际上却一再与中国‘脱钩、切断供应链’，”美国大使馆发言人刘鹏宇在一份声明中表示。 “它不断升级对中国的打压和限制。”</p><p>过去十年中，在习近平政府制定了主导尖端行业的计划，并加大了对外国公司转让专有技术的压力后，有关技术和市场准入的争端已酝酿多年，并在过去十年中爆发为更加激烈的冲突。</p><p>特朗普政府将中国军方供应商列入黑名单并加强对中国在美投资的审查，随后拜登政府又全面禁止先进半导体及其制造设备的转让以及美国公民和永久居民的参与在那个部门。美国还让盟友日本和荷兰效仿。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-bans-micron-as-supplier-to-big-chinese-firms-citing-national-security-5f326b90?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国进行了报复</a>，对对绿色技术至关重要的矿物出口实施管制，并禁止美国芯片制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MU" class="company-name">美光科技</a>在关键基础设施中使用产品。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为中美关系将走向何方？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧，并阻止报复。她说，她解释说，这些措施的目的是缩小范围，是为了国家安全目的，而不是为了经济优势，她预计北京也会这样做。</p><p> “国家安全是我们不能妥协的事情，我们会保护它，即使这会损害我们自己狭隘的经济利益，我们也会这样做。但当我们采取这些确实对中国经济产生影响的行动时，我们将确保这些行动是透明的、目标明确的、解释清楚的，”耶伦上个月在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PARA" class="">哥伦比亚广播</a><span class="company-name-type">公司的</span>“面对国家”节目中表示。 ”</p><p> “我要指出的是，中国也通过出口管制和其他类似手段保护自己的国家安全，”耶伦说。</p><p>尽管中国大使馆周三的声明并未暗示进行报复，但中国官员表示，鉴于习近平优先考虑维护中国利益，北京可能会采取报复行动。如果北京这样做，它可能会谨慎选择，以避免损害本国企业并进一步削弱经济。</p><p>其中一个特别的弱点是电动汽车和太阳能技术，中国在这两个领域的供应链中占据主导地位。保卫民主基金会的皮卡西克表示，他认为投资限制会蔓延开来，影响美国投资者进入其他领域的意愿，特别是生物技术等可以增强军事或警察能力的领域。</p><p> “这里的结构性基本面是竞争和升级，我认为到目前为止，从美国政府围绕这一举措发出的信号、中国的期望和潜在反应来看，我们所看到的任何事情都表明没有任何突破。 ，“ 他说。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Berber Jin、Lingling Wei 和 Vivian Salama 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给查尔斯·赫兹勒 (Charles Hutzler)： <a href="mailto:charles.hutzler@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">charles.hutzler@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:28:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d<author><![CDATA[Charles Hutzler]]></author><category>华尔街日报华盛顿</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>国际关系</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>国际关系</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Ally Promised to Send Aid to Sudan. It Sent Weapons Instead.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>阿联酋的武器运输正在助长一场已造成 3,900 多人死亡的战争，这与拜登政府结束冲突的努力背道而驰<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831056/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="自四月中旬以来，苏丹的战争已造成数千人丧生，并使该国陷入人道主义灾难。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>自四月中旬以来，苏丹的战争已造成数千人丧生，并使该国陷入人道主义灾难。纵梁/Shutterstock<span>纵梁/Shutterstock</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119615"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119615"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/nicholas-bariyo" itemprop="url" rel="author">尼古拉斯·巴里约 (Nicholas Bariyo)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伯努瓦·福孔 (Benoit Faucon)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日上午 12:02（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-u-s-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>乌干达恩德培——六月初，当一架货机降落在乌干达最繁忙的机场时，其飞行文件显示，这架货机载有阿拉伯联合酋长国为苏丹难民提供的人道主义援助物资。</p><p>乌干达官员表示，他们在飞机货舱中发现了数十个绿色塑料箱，里面装满了弹药、突击步枪和其他小型武器，而不是飞机舱单上列出的食品和医疗用品。</p><p> 6 月 2 日在恩德培机场发现的武器是美国盟友阿联酋支持苏丹军阀穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛中将的努力的一部分，后者正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sudan-khartoum-military-what-is-happening-447d40e2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">争夺非洲第三大国的控制权。</a>官员表示。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="462" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831053?width=700&amp;height=462" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛中将是一名军阀，与苏丹军队争夺非洲第三大国的控制权。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：MOHAMED NURELDIN ABDALLAH/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据非营利性武装冲突地点和事件数据项目称，官员们表示，阿联酋的秘密武器运输正在助长一场战争，自<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sudan-rivalry-between-powerful-generals-erupts-in-warfare-3fdf7452?&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">4 月 15 日战争爆发</a>以来，这场战争已<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-other-diplomats-in-sudan-are-attacked-as-violence-flares-6211c1ae?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">使苏丹陷入人道主义灾难</a>，并造成 3,900 多人死亡。武装达加洛的快速支援部队民兵可能会加剧阿联酋和美国之间的摩擦，而美国一直在努力调解结束战争。</p><p>联合国机构和人权组织指责快速支援部队民兵在苏丹侵犯人权，包括杀害平民。</p><p>阿联酋政府在回答《华尔街日报》的提问时表示，它支持和平解决苏丹冲突，并“寻求提供一切形式的支持，以减轻人道主义苦难”。该公司表示，已向受战争影响的人们运送了约 2000 吨人道主义援助物资，包括食品和医疗用品，并在邻国乍得建立了一家野战医院。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831078?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">今年早些时候，阿联酋驻苏丹大使哈马德·穆罕默德·阿尔尼比在苏丹港机场向运送援助物资的飞机机组人员致意。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：穆罕默德·阿里·哈里西/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>无国界医生组织发言人表示，该组织没有从阿联酋获得武器或其他军事物资，并否认其武装分子参与了侵犯人权的行为。</p><p>阿联酋可能押注于达加洛，以帮助保护阿联酋<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/stakes-in-sudans-war-include-russian-gold-nile-dam-key-shipping-lane-e49c0b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在苏丹的利益</a>，因为苏丹位于红海、通往尼罗河的战略位置和巨大的黄金储备。阿联酋的利益包括大片苏丹农田和计划耗资 60 亿美元的红海港口的股份。</p><p>联合国监察员此前<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-a-e-boosted-arms-transfers-tolibyato-salvage-warlords-campaign-u-n-panel-finds-11601412059?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指责阿布扎比向哈利法·哈夫塔尔运送武器</a>，包括无人机、激光制导炸弹和装甲车，</p>苏丹西北部邻国利比亚的一名民兵指挥官。哈夫塔尔和达加洛都曾与俄罗斯瓦格纳集团合作，允许该准军事组织进入<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-oil-grab-in-libya-fuels-u-s-kremlin-tensions-in-mideast-11595772000?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">利比亚的油田</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/who-will-control-wagners-empire-of-war-and-gold-22444d60?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">苏丹的金矿</a>。<p></p><p>据联合国称，达加洛的无国界医生组织和苏丹武装部队之间的战斗已导致超过 400 万人离开家园，而约 2400 万人（约占该国人口的一半） <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cut-off-from-food-and-cash-sudanese-starve-as-fighting-drags-on-eaea355f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">现在需要食物</a>和其他人道主义援助。超过30万名难民逃离无国界医生组织在达尔富尔的据点，越过边境进入乍得。 6 月 2 日航班的舱单将这些货物列为对难民的人道主义援助。</p><p>据包括人权观察在内的当地和国际人权组织称，自四月以来，无国界医生组织战士和当地民兵联盟袭击了城镇和村庄，强奸妇女并杀害了数百名平民。继 7 月发现数个乱葬坑后，国际刑事法院检察官表示，他正在调查达尔富尔地区潜在的新战争罪行，达尔富尔是 2000 年代初期种族灭绝的发生地。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831076?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">苏丹首都喀土穆五月的战斗结束后，浓烟升起。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="729" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832077?width=1260&amp;height=729" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">本月早些时候，逃离冲突的苏丹人越过边境进入乍得。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ZOHRA BENSEMRA/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>自 5 月以来，美国官员与沙特阿拉伯官员一道推动了吉达和谈，但由于无国界医生组织和军方多次违反停火协议，正式谈判于 6 月暂停。</p><p>美国国务院发言人表示：“我们会对有关冲突双方获得任何外部支持的报道感到担忧。” “我们继续与阿联酋和其他一些合作伙伴接触和协调，努力敦促苏丹停止敌对行动和人道主义援助准入。”</p><p>熟悉拜登政府非洲政策的人士表示，华盛顿知道阿联酋向无国界部队运送武器，并已向阿布扎比当局表达了其担忧。</p><p>在 6 月 2 日航班上发现武器和弹药的乌干达官员表示，这架阿联酋飞机被允许继续飞往乍得东部的阿姆贾拉斯国际机场。随后，乌干达官员表示，他们接到上级命令，停止检查从阿联酋经停的航班。最近几周，又增加了数十架航班。</p><p> “我们不被允许再检查这些飞机。他们现在是国防部的责任，”一位官员说。 “我们被警告不要拍照。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831734?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿联酋政府表示，已向苏丹运送了约2000吨人道主义援助物资，包括食品和医疗用品。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：穆罕默德·阿里·哈里西/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌干达国防部发言人表示，恩德培机场负责大量货运航班，但否认有任何飞机使用该机场经乍得向无国界医生组织供应武器。</p><p>在最新的一次交付中，卡车满载军用物资<strong>&nbsp;</strong>这位非洲官员和一名前美国官员表示，7 月最后一周，来自阿联酋的一架飞机离开阿姆贾拉斯机场前往苏丹扎尔克地区，那里是无国界武装力量在达尔富尔北部的一个据点。</p><p>阿联酋的武器交付也引发了人们对乍得政府忠诚度的质疑。美国和法国将乍得总统穆罕默德·代比<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/washingtons-dilemma-in-chad-defense-or-democracy-45b40573?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">视为打击圣战武装分子和俄罗斯在该地区扩张的盟友</a>。</p><p>今年早些时候，美国官员<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-intelligence-points-to-wagner-plot-against-key-western-ally-in-africa-29867547?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">警告代比</a>，瓦格纳老板叶夫根尼·普里戈任正在与乍得叛军合作，破坏其政府的稳定，并可能杀死他。</p><p>然而，熟悉拜登政府政策的人士表示，阿联酋向达加洛运送武器是为了支持瓦格纳在非洲最亲密的合作伙伴之一。乍得信息部长阿齐兹·穆罕默德·萨利赫没有回应置评请求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831069?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">熟悉拜登政府政策的人士表示，阿联酋向穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛的快速支援部队民兵运送武器是为了支持瓦格纳集团在非洲最亲密的合作伙伴之一。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Mahmoud Hjaj/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831737?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在六月的一次会议上，阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬（右）与乍得总统穆罕默德·代比（左）签署了军事、采矿和能源协议。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：hassan al menhali/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬于 6 月 14 日在阿布扎比会见了代比，两位领导人在那里签署了一系列有价值的军事、采矿和能源协议。乌干达官员表示，会议结束后不久，经恩德培飞往乍得的航班变得更加频繁。</p><p>写信给 Nicholas Bariyo <a href="mailto:nicholas.bariyo@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（nicholas.bariyo@wsj.com）</a>和 Benoit Faucon（ <a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:02:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/aus-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/aus-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f<author><![CDATA[Nicholas BariyoBenoit Faucon]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>货运/物流</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>发展/人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>发展</category><category>人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>货运</category><category>后勤</category><category>运输</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ecuadorean Presidential Candidate Assassinated]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>费尔南多·比亚维森西奥 (Fernando Villavicencio) 在谴责贩毒团伙和腐败后，对他收到的威胁置之不理<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123803"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3A297452-49E9-4885-AD64-0A664604940D&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">距离选举不到两周，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥在离开基多的竞选活动时被枪杀。他是腐败的尖锐批评者，并表示他受到了当地帮派的威胁。照片：Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123803"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-dube" itemprop="url" rel="author">瑞安·杜贝</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/juan-forero" itemprop="url" rel="author">胡安·福雷罗</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 9 日晚上 10:11（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索表示，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥于周三被枪杀， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cocaine-trade-and-gang-violence-strike-hard-in-once-peaceful-ecuador-bad953c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">距离</a>该国选举还不到两周。</p><p> 59 岁的前记者兼国会议员比亚维森西奥 (Villavicencio) 在首都基多一所学校参加竞选活动后被杀。</p><p> “对总统候选人费尔南多·维拉维森西奥被暗杀感到愤怒和沮丧，”拉索在 X（该网站以前称为 Twitter）上写道。 “为了纪念他并为了他的斗争，我向你们保证，这一罪行将不会逍遥法外。”</p><p>总检察长办公室称，一名杀人嫌疑人被捕后因伤重死亡。</p><p>网上发布的一段视频显示，比亚维森西奥上车后不久，人们纷纷倒地，枪声响起。比亚维森西奥的朋友、记者克里斯蒂安·苏里塔发布的另一段视频显示，人们尖叫着，挤在学校的地板上。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “他们杀了我的朋友，”祖里塔在发布视频后不久发推文。</p><p>比亚维森西奥严厉批评腐败和贩毒团伙，这些团伙最近在这个曾经相对和平的国家制造了流血事件。他最近表示，他收到了当地一个名为 Choneros 的帮派的威胁。该团伙与墨西哥锡那罗亚贩毒集团有联系，安全专家表示，该集团确保<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">来自哥伦比亚的可卡因运输经过厄瓜多尔</a>，然后向北运往美国</p><p>“这证实了我们的竞选提案将严重影响这些犯罪结构，”他在谈到最近的威胁时说道。 “我不害怕。”</p><p>比亚维森西奥在另一场谈到经济的演讲中表示，“谈论投资需要拆除犯罪结构。”</p><p> “我们的犯罪经济由贩毒、非法采矿和……公共部门腐败贿赂提供资金，”他说。</p><p>拉索呼吁举行新的选举以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-president-dissolves-congress-ahead-of-impeachment-vote-987f5883?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">避免遭到国会弹劾</a>，厄瓜多尔人定于 8 月 20 日投票选举新总统。 Political analysts say that Villavicencio was one of the candidates with a chance to finish second in the first round vote. Polls show that no one is likely to take enough votes to win the presidency outright in the first round. That scenario would require a second-round runoff between the top two candidates. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833069?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> People take cover after Ecuadorean presidential candidate Fernando Villavicencio was shot following a rally in Quito on Wednesday evening.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>The death of Villavicencio led to an outpouring of condolences.</p><p> “As an Ecuadorean, I deeply lament the assassination of Fernando Villavicencio at the hands of criminals,” said another presidential candidate, Jan Topic, in a video posted online. “Today more than ever an iron fist is needed.”</p><p> As a journalist, Villavicencio led numerous investigations and wrote books about government corruption, especially during the administration of former President</p> Rafael Correa, who was convicted in 2020 of corruption in absentia.<p></p><p> Villavicencio was later elected to Congress and led the oversight committee, where he investigated graft. He was a sharp critic of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-global-mega-projects-infrastructure-falling-apart-11674166180?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Chinese loans to Ecuador</a> , including for large hydroelectric projects.</p><p> “Ecuador was harmed,” he told The Wall Street Journal during an interview last year at his congressional office.</p><p> Once one of Latin America&#39;s safest countries, Ecuador has become <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/inside-the-experiment-to-stop-the-carnage-in-latin-america-11546275481?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">one of its most dangerous</a> . Police and security experts say <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">record cocaine production in neighboring Colombia</a> and violence among Ecuadorean drug gangs propped up by Mexican and Albanian cartels has sparked a wave of violence.</p><p> Homicides have quadrupled since 2019, reaching a record 4,800 last year and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/andes-turmoil-rattles-governments-spurs-migration-to-u-s-d8396753?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">driving a surge in migration</a> , mainly to the US, according to the Interior Ministry. Violence has increased significantly since 2020, mostly hitting the coastal city of Guayaquil, as gangs fight for control of cocaine-trafficking routes to maritime ports. Police and residents say that assassins gun down prosecutors and police, hang bodies from bridges and recruit children.</p><p> Write to Ryan Dubé at <a href="mailto:ryan.dube@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.dube@wsj.com</a> and Juan Forero at <a href="mailto:juan.forero@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">juan.forero@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 02:11:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5<author><![CDATA[Ryan DubéJuan Forero]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Corruption</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>Financial Crime</category><category> Gangs</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>选举</category><category>National/Presidential Elections</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>corruption</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>financial crime</category><category> gangs</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>presidential elections </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Haitian Kidnappers Release U.S. Nurse and Her Daughter]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Western Hemisphere&#39;s poorest country is grappling with a wave of criminal gang violence and kidnappings <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122473"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="645" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832829?width=860&amp;height=645" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Alix Dorsainvil, pictured with her husband Sandro Dorsainvil, was kidnapped last month.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: El Roi/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122473"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jose-decordoba" itemprop="url" rel="author">José de Córdoba</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated Aug. 9, 2023 7:30 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-u-s-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> An American nurse and her young daughter were released by their abductors in Haiti on Wednesday after spending nearly two weeks in captivity, victims of rising <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gangs-threaten-to-tip-haiti-into-a-failed-state-11634654955?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">kidnappings and killings</a> in the Western Hemisphere&#39;s poorest country.</p><p> El Roi Haiti, which runs a school for some 400 children near the capital Port-au-Prince, said Alix Dorsainvil, the wife of the organization&#39;s director, and their daughter, were kidnapped on July 27.</p><p> “There is still much to process and to heal from in this situation,” El Roi Haiti said in a statement. The organization said their release brought “gratitude and extreme joy.” No other details were disclosed, including whether a ransom had been paid.</p><p> El Roi Haiti asked that no attempts be made to contact Dorsainvil or her family.</p><p> Haiti has been caught in a spiral of social turmoil and criminal gang violence since the assassination two years ago of the country&#39;s president, Jovenel Moïse. Moïse was killed, and his wife wounded, when more than 20 former Colombian soldiers stormed the presidential compound in July 2021.</p><p> The <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-arrests-florida-businessmen-accused-of-plotting-haiti-presidents-killing-cd21ce08?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">investigation into the assassination</a> has stalled in Haiti, where more than 40 people were initially detained. US prosecutors have made progress in Miami, where one person has pleaded guilty to the killing and 10 others face charges in federal court.</p><p> Kidnappings and killings rose sharply after the assassination as powerful gangs, many with links to corrupt politicians and businessmen, fought for control of Port-au-Prince.</p><p> In a report this week, Unicef recorded almost 300 cases of kidnappings of women and children so far this year, about the same number as in all of 2022 and three times as many as in 2021.</p><p> “The growing trend in kidnappings and abductions is extremely worrisome,” said Garry Conille, Unicef&#39;s regional director for Latin America and the Caribbean.</p><p> The deterioration of Haiti&#39;s security and economy has put some 5.2 million people, including three million children, about half the country&#39;s population at risk, Unicef said.</p><p> Dorsainvil, who is originally from New Hampshire, had been working as a school nurse at El Roi Haiti since 2020 and had married the organization&#39;s director in 2021, the school said. She first started coming to Haiti in the aftermath of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703798904575069614263432520?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the 2010 earthquake</a> , which is estimated to have killed more than 200,000 people.</p><p> Last month, on the same day that Dorsainvil was kidnapped, the US Embassy ordered the departure of all nonemergency personnel from the country.</p><p> The Center for Analysis and Research in Human Rights, a Haitian organization that tracks kidnappings, says there have been 539 kidnappings in the country since January, including at least 51 of foreigners.</p><p> “The situation suggests an increase in violence and other gang activities for the third quarter,” the center said.</p><p> Last year, Haiti&#39;s prime minister, Ariel Henry, asked the United Nations and the international community <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-n-considers-sanctions-international-mission-to-restore-security-in-haiti-11666199198?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to send a security force</a> to help the outgunned and outmanned Haitian police tame the country&#39;s violent gangs, which some analysts say control about 80% of the capital and are extending their reach into the nation&#39;s countryside.</p><p> The US and Canada have been unwilling to head such a mission, but last month the government of Kenya said it would be willing to do so, and would commit up to 1,000 Kenyan police officers to assist Haitian police. Kenya said it would send an exploratory mission to Haiti by mid-August. The Bahamas has agreed to contribute some 150 officers.</p><p> US Secretary of State Antony Blinken said the US would push for a UN Security Council resolution authorizing a multinational force for Haiti.</p><p> In October 2021, the kidnapping of 17 US and Canadian missionaries, including four children and an 8-month old baby, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/haiti-missionaries-kidnapping-11634584227?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">captured the world&#39;s attention</a> . The missionaries were released over the next two months. The kidnappers had demanded a ransom of $1 million per captive, but it wasn&#39;t clear whether a ransom was paid.</p><p> Write to José de Córdoba at <a href="mailto:jose.decordoba@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jose.decordoba@wsj.com</a></p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>The last name of US Secretary of State Antony Blinken was given incorrectly as Blilnken in an earlier version of this article. (Corrected on Aug. 9)</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 23:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-us-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-us-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263<author><![CDATA[José de Córdoba]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>Gangs</category><category> Kidnapping/Abduction</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>gangs</category><category> kidnapping</category><category> abduction</category><category>犯罪企业</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Colombian Rebels Are Accused of Plot to Kill Attorney General]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> ELN allegedly planned to assassinate top prosecutor as group prepared for cease-fire agreement <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123265"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832963?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The alleged plot against Attorney General Francisco Barbosa was denied by the ELN guerrilla group.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: daniel munoz/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123265"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 9, 2023 6:20 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-rebels-are-accused-of-plotting-to-kill-attorney-general-68789dc0"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> BOGOTÁ, Colombia—Five high-ranking Colombian rebels met in Venezuela to hatch a plot to assassinate the Colombian attorney general as their ELN guerrilla group prepared to embark on <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-government-and-leftist-rebels-begin-cease-fire-c73bf849?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">peace talks</a> with the Bogotá government, his chief deputy said Wednesday.</p><p> Deputy Attorney General Martha Mancera said that prosecutors are investigating a plan in which a guerrilla sharpshooter would be used to kill her boss, Attorney General Francisco Barbosa. Her announcement came days after the ELN, which stands for National Liberation Army, entered into a six-month bilateral cease-fire agreement with President Gustavo Petro as a prelude to peace negotiations to end the group&#39;s 59-year conflict with the state.</p><p> “We began to obtain information from sources 30 days ago,” Mancera told reporters in the Colombian capital, Bogotá.</p><p> No attack has been launched against Barbosa. His office said his security detail is now being reinforced.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> The ELN, a Cuba-inspired group that operates in several regions of Colombia and in Venezuela, said on social media that the news was false and intended to “sabotage the dialogue that is developing between the government and the ELN.”</p><p> The attorney general&#39;s office said in a statement that separate warnings about the plot came from its own investigative arm, the intelligence division of Colombia&#39;s Armed Forces and a police unit that investigates organized crime.</p><p> Officials said that the planned attack on Barbosa was to be carried out by a member of an ELN urban unit under the command of a man only known by his alias, Rolo. The attorney general&#39;s office said that suspicious financial transactions worth about $750,000 and linked to Rolo had been detected, moving in a way similar to the transactions that investigators had seen with an ELN unit accused in the 2019 bombing of a police academy in Bogotá in which 22 cadets were killed.</p><p> “According to the information from sources in the neighboring country of Venezuela, meetings were held that had to do with the possible preparation and execution of the attack against the attorney general,” Mancera said.</p><p> Colombian Foreign Minister Álvaro Leyva, who has worked on trying to advance talks between guerrilla groups and the government, said that the allegations needed to be investigated carefully because “this could perfectly be a bomb against the peace process.”</p><p> “It&#39;s important to establish the truth,” he said.</p><p> Otty Patiño, the government&#39;s chief negotiator with the ELN, told Colombia&#39;s Blu Radio that the allegations are “very serious because they also compromise Venezuela at a time when relations with that country are being resumed.”</p><p> Venezuela&#39;s government, headed by President Nicolás Maduro, didn&#39;t return messages seeking comment. His regime has in recent years deepened <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/venezuela-gives-colombian-rebels-free-rein-11563105600?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">ties with the ELN</a> , giving the group free rein to run wildcat gold mines and traffic drugs in Venezuela in exchange for providing muscle for the government, Colombian and US officials have said.</p><p> It couldn&#39;t be determined what the motivation would be to attack Barbosa. He has in the past raised questions on government plans to be lenient with members of armed groups that surrender. But he has also lifted warrants on 29 ELN rebels to permit them to engage in talks with the president&#39;s negotiators.</p><p> “A big reason why there are negotiations in which a peace process is being discussed is because the attorney general&#39;s office has suspended arrest warrants against those people,” Mancera said.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Jenny Carolina González contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Juan Forero at <a href="mailto:juan.forero@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">juan.forero@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:20:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-rebels-are-accused-of-plotting-to-kill-attorney-general-68789dc0</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-rebels-are-accused-of-plotting-to-kill-attorney-general-68789dc0<category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>国际关系</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Brazil’s Bet on Oil in the Amazon Meets Resistance]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> President da Silva&#39;s plan to drill draws criticism from Colombian leader, environmentalists <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831866/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Brazilian oil company Petrobras is seeking permission to drill near the mouth of the Amazon River." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Brazilian oil company Petrobras is seeking permission to drill near the mouth of the Amazon River. Pilar Olivares/REUTERS <span>Pilar Olivares/REUTERS</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122539"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122539"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/samantha-pearson" itemprop="url" rel="author">萨曼莎·皮尔森</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/luciana-magalhaes" itemprop="url" rel="author">卢西亚娜·马加哈斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Updated Aug. 9, 2023 6:07 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-bet-on-oil-in-the-amazon-meets-resistance-a14a544e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> SÃO PAULO—Brazilian President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva has positioned himself as a global leader in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazilian-president-elect-luiz-inacio-lula-da-silva-says-he-will-end-illegal-amazon-deforestation-11672336459?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the fight against climate change</a> , pledging at a summit of South American leaders this week <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/latin-american-countries-aim-to-curb-amazon-deforestation-c479cfd5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to fight deforestation</a> as part of “a new Amazonian dream.”</p><p> There is a significant contradiction, environmentalists say.</p><p> Da Silva also backs plans by state-controlled oil company <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PBR" class="company-name">Petrobras</a> to open up the Amazon <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-petrobras-to-end-market-friendly-fuel-pricing-92359c48?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to oil exploration</a> to position Brazil as one of the world&#39;s biggest oil producers.</p><p> As other countries have tried to transition from fossil fuels, Brazil, which has 15 billion barrels of proven reserves and an economy reliant on fossil fuels, has in recent years <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/petrobras-exxonmobil-shell-chevron-among-winners-of-brazil-pre-salt-auction-1538143301?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">tapped oil in the Atlantic</a> , passing Kuwait to become the world&#39;s ninth-biggest producer, according to the Energy Institute&#39;s Statistical Review of World Energy.</p><p> By opening up new fields in the Amazon and elsewhere, the government says it hopes to make a country that is the largest producer in Latin America the world&#39;s fourth-biggest in the next decade. Of the 30 biggest global oil and gas projects approved last year or expected to get the green light this year, Brazil is home to five, ranking only below Saudi Arabia and Qatar, according to Rystad Energy, a Norwegian consulting firm. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832865?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Brazilian President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva attended a summit of Amazon leaders, which closed Wednesday without consensus on oil exploration.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Filipe Bispo/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="708" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832928?width=1260&amp;height=708" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A drilling vessel was anchored in June off the coast of Rio de Janeiro state. Brazil&#39;s economy depends on its fossil-fuel reserves.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Dado Galdieri/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In a country that characterizes itself as a leader in the fight against deforestation, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-lula-makes-remarkable-return-to-power-after-12-years-11672580196?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Brazil&#39;s energy ambitions</a> raise questions about its role in heading off global warming. Like other developing countries, Brazil is struggling both with international demands to protect the world&#39;s biggest rainforest and the needs of its own people, who want economic development and prosperity.</p><p> The two-day summit of the countries that share the Amazon came to an end Wednesday in the Brazilian city of Belém without any agreement over deforestation targets. Participants also failed to reach a consensus on oil exploration, while Colombian President Gustavo Petro, whose government <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/oil-exporting-colombia-says-no-to-oil-exploration-11674930322?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has stopped issuing new oil-exploration licenses</a> , has called for a moratorium in the Amazon.</p><p> Brazilian officials say the country&#39;s future prosperity is tied to oil and gas production.</p><p> “Brazilians have the right to see the country reach its potential,” Energy Minister Alexandre Silveira said Monday before the summit. He argued that Petrobras should be allowed to prospect for oil in Brazil&#39;s Equatorial Margin, a 1,400-mile strip that includes the northern coastlines of six Amazonian states and the mouth of the Amazon River. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832868?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Brazil&#39;s Port of Acu is used as a base for offshore oil operations.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Maria Magdalena Arrellaga/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Amazonian oil could be a game changer for Brazil, proponents of more production assert. The Equatorial Margin could contain 30 billion barrels of crude and oil equivalent, matching about 70% of total US reserves, according to estimates by the Brazilian government.</p><p> A vast country that relies on long-distance trucks and agricultural machinery, Brazil will likely depend on oil for as much as the next 50 years, said Saverio Minervini, an oil expert at Fitch Ratings in New York. The country&#39;s vehicle fleet won&#39;t go electric soon, he added.</p><p> “You can&#39;t operate a tractor in the middle of the savanna and then stop harvesting soy and corn to go plug it in,” Minervini said. Brazil&#39;s domestic demand is so great that without new oil reserves the country risks becoming a net importer of oil between 2030 and 2035, he said, a scenario that economists say could boost inflation, eroding incomes and worsening poverty rates.</p><p> Still, Brazil&#39;s environmental-protection agency, Ibama, in May rejected a request from Petrobras to drill near the mouth of the Amazon River, citing incomplete information in the company&#39;s environmental study of the area.</p><p> But da Silva said in an interview this month broadcast over radio stations in the Amazon that Petrobras was tweaking its application to gain approval.</p><p> “You can keep dreaming about this and I also want to,” da Silva said of the plans. The president said he hopes oil production will create jobs in the poor north and northeastern regions, a swath that is home to one-third of Brazil&#39;s population and three-quarters of the country&#39;s poor. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832842?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Brazilian shipyard workers prepare an offshore oil vessel for use by Petrobras.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: RICARDO MORAES/REUTERS </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832914?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Indigenous people marched in Belém, Brazil, as an Amazon leaders summit opened in the city on Tuesday.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：UESLEI MARCELINO/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Environmentalists and members of da Silva&#39;s administration have expressed strong misgivings.</p><p> “Even if we manage to reduce deforestation by 100%, if the world does not halt the emission of fossil fuels, we will damage the Amazon all the same,” Brazilian Environment Minister</p> Marina Silva said Monday.<p></p><p> While Ecuador, Colombia and other countries already extract oil in the Amazon, the Equatorial Margin extends across a particularly sensitive part of the forest—the mouth of the Amazon River, which carries the largest volume of freshwater in the world, according to the National Aeronautics and Space Administration&#39;s Earth Observatory. The coast of the Amazon is biodiverse, home to some 80% of Brazil&#39;s mangroves, as well as coral reefs.</p><p> Some 80 environmental groups, including Greenpeace and the World Wildlife Fund, wrote a joint letter to Ibama in April calling on the agency to reject Petrobras&#39;s request to start drilling at a block awarded to the company in 2013.</p><p> “Just when the exploration of fossil fuels has pushed the planet towards a climate crisis…the plan to drill new oil wells in search of oil and gas at the mouth of the Amazon is of grave concern,” the groups wrote.</p><p> Da Silva has said that he sees no environmental risks from extracting oil in the region. Environmentalists counter that the precedent isn&#39;t good. Between 1997 and 2021, there were some 600 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/oil-spill-in-peru-could-tarnish-repsols-green-credentials-esg-insight-11643288826?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">oil spills in the Peruvian Amazon</a> , according to a recent report by Oxfam, while pipe ruptures have spewed thousands of barrels of oil <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/litigation-without-end-chevron-battles-on-in-28-year-old-ecuador-lawsuit-11619975500?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">into the forest in Ecuador</a> . </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="431" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832870?width=700&amp;height=431" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A view of Amazon forest in Brazil&#39;s state of Pará, where Belém is the capital city.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：安东尼奥·拉塞尔达/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Colombian leader Petro has called for all new oil developments <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombia-election-weighs-on-future-of-oil-sector-11655397102?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to be blocked in the Amazon</a> , taking a jab at da Silva&#39;s government during the summit by implying the Brazilian leftist was repeating the errors of former President Jair Bolsonaro, a conservative who promoted development in the Amazon. Producing oil in the Amazon represents an “enormous ethical conflict, especially for progressive forces that should be on the side of science,” Petro said.</p><p> Though da Silva has promised a radical <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazil-is-key-to-slowing-global-warming-but-its-carbon-market-has-struggled-36a79fde?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">departure on environmental policy</a> after Bolsonaro&#39;s administration, which recorded a sharp rise in deforestation, both leaders share common ground, political scientists said.</p><p> Just as da Silva said Tuesday that the Amazon “is not just about flora and fauna,” but a region in need of jobs and development, Bolsonaro also defended greater use of the region&#39;s resources to spur the economy. Both argued that richer nations must pay Brazil to help fight deforestation.</p><p> “Lula is simply following the country&#39;s historic position on the Amazon…that the region is not destined to become a nature reserve, but is a source of natural resources to be used for economic and social development,” said Rafael Cortez, a political scientist at São Paulo-based consulting firm Tendências.</p><p> Brazil isn&#39;t alone in struggling to balance curtailing global warming with delivering a growing economy, said Christopher Garman, managing director for the Americas at Eurasia Group. Many European nations, facing fuel shortages because of Russia&#39;s war in Ukraine, turned back to coal, a source of pollution.</p><p> “Energy security is not always consistent with the full scope of countries&#39; environmental agendas,” said Garman. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832864?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A refinery in Cubatão, near the Brazilian coastline.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: nelson almeida/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>写信给 Samantha Pearson（ <a href="mailto:samantha.pearson@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">samantha.pearson@wsj.com）</a>和 Luciana Magalhaes（ <a href="mailto:luciana.magalhaes@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">luciana.magalhaes@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-bet-on-oil-in-the-amazon-meets-resistance-a14a544e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-bet-on-oil-in-the-amazon-meets-resistance-a14a544e<author><![CDATA[Samantha PearsonLuciana Magalhaes]]></author><category>活力</category><category>Oil and Gas Upstream Operations</category><category> Oil Exploration</category><category> Oil and Gas Exploration</category><category> Fossil Fuels</category><category> Oil and Gas</category><category> Oil</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Climate Change</category><category>自然环境</category><category>森林砍伐</category><category>全球/世界问题</category><category>环境保护</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Petroleo Brasileiro S/A Pref</category><category> PETR4.BR</category><category> BR:PETR4</category><category> Petrobras</category><category>路易斯·伊纳西奥·卢拉·达席尔瓦</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>自然环境</category><category>砍伐森林</category><category>全球的</category><category>世界问题</category><category>environmental p